*She simply kept walking towards him until she stopped near enough to him to 
touch,tired and damaged just like him. Something in common if nothing else.
But before Prowl could do anything she walked a bit to the near wall and 
smalled her damaged shoulder up against it with a sickening pop, meaning 
that it was no relocated...but hurt like Hell!!!

She yipped a bit and growled, but that was it. Though, she was limping far 
more worse now then before.
With a heaved sigh she simply moved towards Prowl again, not seeing the hand 
he held out to touch her until it actually did.
She flinched a bit but she was so tired she didn't care...as long as he 
didn't try and pick her up or anything.

She whimpered a bit as she just stood there, looking at the floor. She hurt 
and she didn't like it, and Prowl was hurt and she didn't like it.
And most of all, she was so confused.*
